approveByWhitelistedContract(address,add.details: This function is used by RestakingConnector.sol to approve Eigenlayer StrategyManager to transfer and EigenAgent's tokens into Eigenlayer strategy vaults. This avoids needing extra transfers and signed messages to complete L2 restaking deposits.

params.amount: of tokens user is depositing into the strategy vault.
params.spenderContract: to approve transfer for, expected to be the Eigenlayer StrategyManager contract
params.token: the token used in the Eigenlayer Strategy vault.

createEigenAgentCallDigestHash(address,u.details: Creates a digestHash of the Eigenlayer command (e.g depositIntoStrategy) to be sent through CCIP.

params.chainid: is the chain EigenAgent and Eigenlayer is deployed on.
params.data: to send (e.g. encoded queueWithdrawal parameters) to target contract (DelegationManager)
params.expiry: expiry parameter for signature (currently does not revert if expired)
params.nonce: execution nonce used in EigenAgent execution signatures
params.target: contract for the EigenAgent to call
params.value: amount of Eth to send with the call

params.chainid: is the chain Eigenlayer and EigenAgent are deployed on.

executeWithSignature(address,uint256,byt.details: EigenAgent receives messages (data) and executes commands on behalf of it's owner on L2. The EigenAgent will only execute if provided a valid signature from the owner of the EigenAgentOwner721 NFT associated with the ERC-6551 EigenAgent account.

params.data: the data (message) to send to targetContract (e.g. depositIntoStrategy calldata)
params.expiry: expiry of the signature, currently only used to give users an option to withdraw bridged funds (for a deposit) if the call reverts after a period of a time (e.g in case an Operator deactivates in the time it takes to bridge from L2 to L1 and deposit).
params.signature: is the owner of the EigenAgent's signature, signed over the hash of the data that the EigenAgent calls the targetContract with.
params.value: amount of ETH to send with the call

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).details: Checks if signature is valid according to ERC-1271. If the signer is an EOA, it validates signatures using ecrecover. If the signer is a contract, calls isValidSignature on the contract to determin if the signatuer is valid. For an example, see MockMultisigSigner.sol contract and associated tests.

setInitialRestakingConnector(address).details: Initializes the EigenAgent6551 with a RestakingConnector address

params._restakingConnector: The address of the RestakingConnector contract

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[EIP section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

EIGEN_AGENT_EXEC_TYPEHASH().notice: The EIP-712 typehash for the deposit struct used by the contract

restakingConnector().notice: Only the RestakingConnector address can call executeWithSignature
